15.40	New_Laws	New Laws	The New Laws, in Spanish Leyes Nuevas, issued November 20, 1542 by King Charles V of Spain regarding the Spanish colonization of the Americas, are also known as the "New Laws of the Indies for the Good Treatment and Preservation of the Indians", and were created to prevent the exploitation of the Indigenous peoples of the Americas by the Encomenderos (large enterprise landowners) by strictly limiting their power and dominion.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Leyes_Nuevas1.jpg/225px-Leyes_Nuevas1.jpg
